15/06/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Macedonian Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski and NATO Secretary General George Robertson discussed reforms within the Macedonian defence sector as well as the country's progress in implementing the Ohrid peace accord, during a meeting Friday (13 June) in Brussels. 
They also agreed that there are no serious threats of destabilisation in Macedonia. 
Afterwards, Buckovski met with his Turkish counterpart, Vecdi Gonul, to discuss increased Turkish military assistance to the Macedonian Army in 2004. 
While in Brussels, Buckovski also participated in a trilateral meeting with his counterparts from Albania and Croatia, Pandeli Majko and Zeljka Antunovic. 
(MIA - 13/06/03)
